liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Mitch Starc gets a little clip up in the air and the ball goes to backward leg gully. Harry Brook tore after it, stopped when he saw how close it was to Bairstow, who then just refused to run to it, and had to go again, dive, and take a brilliant catch. Wow, I'm not sure what Bairstow was doing there, it's fallen about 2 or 3 metres away from him and it a keepers catch, with the gloves, all day. But he left it to Brook and perhaps that was for the best given his record with the gloves this series, it was a nice catch. "For me, that was Bairstow's catch," Glenn McGrath says. "The confidence of Bairstow at the minute, he probably wanted to let Harry Brook take that." A useful 16 runs off 19 balls.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: OUT! STARC IS CAUGHT!

children.content: Mitch Starc gets a little clip up in the air and the ball goes to backward leg gully.
Harry Brook tore after it, stopped when he saw how close it was to Bairstow, who then just refused to run to it, and had to go again, dive, and take a brilliant catch.
Wow, I'm not sure what Bairstow was doing there, it's fallen about 2 or 3 metres away from him and it a keepers catch, with the gloves, all day.
But he left it to Brook and perhaps that was for the best given his record with the gloves this series, it was a nice catch.
"For me, that was Bairstow's catch," Glenn McGrath says.
"The confidence of Bairstow at the minute, he probably wanted to let Harry Brook take that."

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Carey tries to leave the ball outside off, it was tight though and he didn't get his bat out the way enough and he's played on. There was some swing there from Woakes again, who has found his groove here, but that did bounce up again. "There's a little bit of variable bounce in this pitch," says Glenn McGarth on ABC/BBC radio. "That one bounced more than Carey expected. "Every run Australia get now will be valuable. The lead is only 165. England are right in this game now." Carey goes for five.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: BOWLED HIM! CAREY HAS TO GO!

children.content: Carey tries to leave the ball outside off, it was tight though and he didn't get his bat out the way enough and he's played on.
There was some swing there from Woakes again, who has found his groove here, but that did bounce up again.
"There's a little bit of variable bounce in this pitch," says Glenn McGarth on ABC/BBC radio.
"That one bounced more than Carey expected.
"Every run Australia get now will be valuable. The lead is only 165. England are right in this game now."

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Just a feather! Marsh tries to leave it outside off but the ball came up a bit more off the pitch and clipped the glove. Marsh goes for 28.
